---
/**
 * about.astro — About Discover Arizona
 * Route: /about
 * Content: Scott's personal story
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import scottImg from '../../images/scott-murray.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Scott"
  description="I'm Scott — a travel writer from Southern California who fell in love with Arizona's deserts, canyons, and wide-open spaces. This is the story behind Discover Arizona."
>

<!-- ═══════════════ HERO ═══════════════ -->
<section class="about-hero">
  <video class="about-hero-video" autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata">
    <source src="/videos/pillar/about-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  </video>
  <div class="about-hero-gradient-overlay"></div>
  <div class="hero-grid"></div>
  <div class="about-hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">About Discover Arizona</div>
    <h1>One Writer, One Desert, <em>Endless Roads</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-intro">I'm Scott — a Southern California guy who drove to Arizona on a whim one weekend and never stopped going back. The Grand Canyon changed something in me. Then Sedona did it again. Then Monument Valley. Then a random dirt road outside Bisbee at sunset. What started as weekend road trips turned into an obsession with this state's landscapes, history, and small towns. This site is everything I've learned — the real version, not the brochure version.</p>
    <div class="hero-line"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ PERSONAL STORY ═══════════════ -->
<section class="letter-section reveal">
  <div class="letter-block">
    <div class="letter-attr">Scott <span class="attr-role">· American · Based in Southern California · Exploring Arizona since the early 2000s</span></div>
    <p class="letter-text">I work in healthcare IT. I'm not a travel blogger or influencer — I'm a guy who plans trips obsessively and finally decided to put it all somewhere useful. Arizona grabbed me the way some places just do. The first time I stood at the South Rim of the Grand Canyon, I understood why people get emotional about rocks. The first time I drove through Monument Valley at dawn, I pulled over and just sat there for twenty minutes.<br><br>I've driven thousands of miles across this state — the interstates, the back highways, the forest roads north of Flagstaff, the mining-town switchbacks around Bisbee. I've hiked in summer heat that nearly broke me and watched snow fall on red rocks in Sedona in January. I've eaten at roadside diners, splurged at Scottsdale resorts, and camped under more stars than I knew existed near Page.<br><br><strong>Discover Arizona exists because I got tired of generic travel content.</strong> The "Top 10 Things to Do" lists that all say the same thing. The sponsored hotel reviews. The articles clearly written by someone who spent one afternoon at each place. I wanted to build the resource I wished I had when I first started exploring — real prices, real logistics, honest opinions, and an AI trip planner that actually knows the difference between Tucson in March and Tucson in August.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ PROFILE CARD ═══════════════ -->
<section class="profiles-section">
  <div class="profiles-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Meet the Writer</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The Person Behind the Pages</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="profiles-grid">
    <div class="profile-card reveal">
      <div class="profile-banner scott"><div class="profile-banner-bg"></div></div>
      <Image src={scottImg} alt="Scott Murray" class="profile-avatar scott-av" width={96} height={96} format="webp" loading="lazy" />
      <div class="profile-body">
        <div class="profile-name">Scott</div>
        <div class="profile-role">Founder · Writer · Videographer</div>
        <p class="profile-bio">Healthcare IT professional by day, Arizona travel obsessive by every other waking moment. Based in Southern California. Has driven every major highway and most of the back roads across Arizona. Loves the desert, the canyons, the old mining towns, and the feeling of a two-lane highway with nobody else on it. Built Discover Arizona because the resource he wanted didn't exist yet.</p>
        <div class="profile-stats">
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">12</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Destinations covered</div></div>
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">1000s</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Miles driven in AZ</div></div>
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">40+</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Countries traveled</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ OUR PROMISE ═══════════════ -->
<section class="promise-section">
  <div class="promise-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">My Promise</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What You'll Never Find Here</h2>
    <p class="promise-text">I built this site because I got tired of Arizona travel content that's secretly a press trip recap or a sponsored hotel review dressed up as honest advice. Discover Arizona exists because I wanted the resource I wished I had when I first started exploring this state.</p>
    <div class="zero-grid">
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num coral">0</div><div class="zero-label">Sponsored posts<br><em>ever</em></div></div>
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num teal">0</div><div class="zero-label">Press trips or<br>free hotel stays</div></div>
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num gold">1000s</div><div class="zero-label">Miles driven<br>across Arizona</div></div>
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num white-num">100%</div><div class="zero-label">Real prices<br>in USD</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="promise-quote">If I recommend it, I've been there. If I list a price, I've paid it. If I tell you to skip something, I've wasted my own money there first.</div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ WHAT WE'RE BUILDING ═══════════════ -->
<section class="vision-section">
  <div class="vision-inner">
    <div class="vision-content">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">What I'm Building</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">More Than a Travel Blog</h2>
      <p class="vision-text">Discover Arizona isn't a collection of "Top 10" listicles. It's a living resource built on real experience and technology that actually helps you plan a better trip. Here's what makes it different:</p>
      <ul class="vision-list">
        <li><span class="v-icon">&#127909;</span> Video guides for select destinations — see the canyons, trails, and towns before you book</li>
        <li><span class="v-icon">&#129302;</span> An AI trip planner that builds custom itineraries with real prices, not hallucinated estimates</li>
        <li><span class="v-icon">&#128176;</span> Every price listed in USD, updated regularly based on what I actually pay</li>
        <li><span class="v-icon">&#128663;</span> Driving routes, logistics, and the practical details that turn a trip from stressful to seamless</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a href="/plan/" class="btn-primary">Try the AI Trip Planner</a>
        <a href="/destinations/" class="btn-outline">Browse All Destinations</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vision-features">
      <a href="/destinations/" class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">&#127956;</div><div class="v-feature-title">Destination Guides</div><div class="v-feature-desc">Deep dives into each destination — not surface-level overviews, but real detail with logistics and honest opinions.</div></a>
      <div class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">&#128249;</div><div class="v-feature-title">Video Content</div><div class="v-feature-desc">Real footage from the Grand Canyon, Sedona, Monument Valley, and more. See it before you go.</div></div>
      <a href="/plan/" class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">&#128506;</div><div class="v-feature-title">AI Trip Planner</div><div class="v-feature-desc">Describe your dream trip and get a custom day-by-day itinerary built on real experience.</div></a>
      <div class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">&#128231;</div><div class="v-feature-title">Itinerary Downloads</div><div class="v-feature-desc">PDF itineraries you can take offline — complete with maps, booking links, and insider tips.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ EMAIL CTA ═══════════════ -->
<section class="email-cta-section">
  <div class="email-cta-inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Get the Guide Before Everyone Else</h2>
    <p class="email-cta-desc">I'm building new destination guides, video content, and trip planner features every month. Drop your email and I'll send the good stuff first — no spam, no affiliate dumps, just real Arizona travel intel.</p>
    <form class="email-form" onsubmit="event.preventDefault();">
      <input type="email" class="email-input" placeholder="your@email.com" />
      <button type="submit" class="btn-sand">Subscribe &rarr;</button>
    </form>
    <p class="email-note">I respect your inbox. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  if (!window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
    const ro = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
      entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) e.target.classList.add('visible'); });
    }, { threshold: 0.1, rootMargin: '0px 0px -40px 0px' });
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => ro.observe(el));
  } else {
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => el.classList.add('visible'));
  }
</script>

<style>
  /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     HERO
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════ */
